Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Container extension not installing

Solution: Check Firefox version (must be 57+), restart browser after installation
Issue: Python scripts not opening Firefox tabs

Solution: Verify Firefox is in PATH, check subprocess command syntax, ensure Firefox is not already running in safe mode
Issue: Cannot find Firefox profile directory

Solution: Run firefox -P to see profile locations, check ~/.mozilla/firefox directory exists
Issue: Containers not maintaining isolation

Solution: Verify extension is enabled, check Firefox privacy settings, restart browser
Conclusion
This lab introduced container-based workflows for secure OSINT research. You learned to:

Configure Firefox Multi-Account Containers for research compartmentalization
Implement secure browsing practices using container isolation
Automate container management with Python scripts
Monitor container health and security
Container isolation is essential for maintaining operational security during OSINT investigations. By separating research activities into dedicated containers, you prevent cross-contamination of cookies, sessions, and tracking data.

